CueSports International - formerly World Billiard TV - hosts the largest collection of billiard, pool and cue sports matches on YouTube, with over 1,600 videos uploaded since 2014, live streaming of professional and league pool tournaments!

► If you enjoy watching 8-Ball, 9-Ball, 10-Ballplayed at the highest level, we upload regularly pool and billiard content, including live and exclusive features.

► To be notified of all new upload and LIVE events, click the  🔔 icon next to the Subscribe button.

CueSports International (CSI) is an international pool league and event leader and is the parent company of the BCA Pool League & USA Pool League. For more information about CSI or any of its leagues or events, visit www.playcsipool.com or find CueSports International on Facebook, YouTube, and Instagram.

data.description: Welcome to my billiards channel. I have *personally* edited for continuity & *instructional value* ALL of my pool videos -- a 42-year historical compilation of televised professional players competing for sizable Winner prizes & recognition of their skills by worldwide audiences. Well-known professional players competing from the 1980s onward, are on colorful display. You'll gain a huge amount of valuable pool knowledge from the expert commentary & instantly tele-strated graphics. Your own skills rapidly progress if you closely observe their techniques & strategies for navigating each rack. Also instructional (and popular) are *my* thousands of very thorough replies to viewers' questions. Even people who don't play, will enjoy watching the world's best players & excited reactions of audiences around the world, following the action & their heroes. Enjoy this colorful overview of the world of televised professional pool, its *history* & the uncanny skills of the players! -- Ray Carlton
data.title: ray carlton billiards

Max Eberle is an American Professional Pool Player and coach for over 30 years.  See links for his books below.
Max has been ranked #3 in the world rankings in 2003 and finished ranked 5th on the UPA Tour for two straight years, 2003 & 2004.  More recently he represented the USA with the Mosconi Cup team in the Dream Challenge in Moscow, Russia where he defeated Fedor Gorst in his live televised match, catapulting team USA to a 6-4 lead in the event which team USA went on to win.  Max is the 2013 World 10-foot table 14.1 Champion at the Derby City Classic Straight Pool Challenge, a 2-time national collegiate champion 93’ & 94,’ and the BCA  Junior National Champion in 1991.
data.title: Max Eberle

data.description: Fabio Petroni was born in 1972 in Rome Italy and began playing billiards when he was 13 years old. He won his first Italian Championship in 1993, and has recently won 5 Italian Championships. He went professional in 1998, and came in 2nd place in the European Championship and also in the World Pool League. In 1998 he also became a member of the Mosconi Cup. As 2001 got underway Petroni took first place in the Euro Tour in England. Petroni is known for his trick shot and displayed this when he won The World Pool- trick shot competition in 2001. In 2002 he came in second place in this competition. Petroni later earned 5th place in the US Open in 2002. He has come up against the best players, including Efren Reyes, Johnny Archer, Earl Strickland and Francisco Bustamante. He struggled to become a strong player in his country while much of the general public was unfamiliar the style of pool playing. continue....
data.title: Fabio Petroni
